tp:taxonomyPackage.tp:name: The annual US-GAAP Taxonomy
tp:taxonomyPackage.tp:description: The 2020 U.S. Financial Reporting Taxonomy (Taxonomy) contains updates for accounting standards and other improvements since the 2018 Taxonomy as used by issuers filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC).

tp:entryPoint.tp:description: This entry point includes the elements for the US GAAP Financial Reporting Taxonomy with their standard, period start, period end, total, axis default, and documentation labels. This entry point also includes the following non industry/statement and non disclosure presentation and definition linkbases: 999000 - Deprecated - Deprecated Concepts (presentation) 999000 - Deprecated - Deprecated Concepts (definition). This entry pint also includes Change notes, Implementation notes, and Implementation note relationships
